.SH DESCRIPTION
yabdialog v0.1
by Michel Clasquin\-Johnson <clasqm@gmail.com>
.PP
yabdialog is a CLI utility that displays a variety of dialogs, alerts and panels
with more control over color and placement than you get with the standard
Haiku alert and filepanel commands. It also contains additional widgets.
.PP
The yabdialog command should be  callable from any scripting language that
can issue a SYSTEM call and receive string data back from standard input.
.PP
All parameters must be supplied, in the correct order. Some error\-checking
is performed, but things will get unpredictable if you swop parameters. On
the bright side, all parameters are case\-insensitive.
.PP
yabdialog \fB\-\-colorcontrol\fR white|yellow|red|blue|green|purple|boring
yabdialog \fB\-\-colorcontrol\fR custom <red> <green> <blue>
.PP
WIDGETS
.HP
\fB\-s\fR   \fB\-\-SimpleAlert\fR: A simple fixed\-size Alert box with a
.IP
single OK Button. Good for 140 characters, after
which the message will be truncated.
Returns: Nothing
.HP
\fB\-y\fR   \fB\-\-YesNoAlert\fR: A simple fixed\-size Alert box with 2
.IP
buttons for Yes and No. Good for 140 characters,
after which the message will be truncated.
Returns: "yes" or "no"
.HP
\fB\-o\fR   \fB\-\-OKCancelAlert\fR: Like YesNoAlert, but with buttons
.IP
that read OK and Cancel
Returns: "ok" or "cancel"
.HP
\fB\-e\fR   \fB\-\-Editor\fR: A multiline text editing box. Cut and paste
.IP
is available via a right\-click
Returns: Contents of the edited text
.HP
\fB\-t\fR   \fB\-\-TextInput\fR: A single\-line text editing box. Cut and paste
.IP
is available via a right\-click
Returns: Contents of the edited text
.HP
\fB\-c\fR   \fB\-\-Calendar\fR: Displays a calendar widget.
.IP
Returns: The selected date in the specified format.
.HP
\fB\-r\fR   \fB\-\-RadioBox\fR: Create a window with up to 5 radiobuttons
.IP
Returns: the number of the selected button. If nothing was
selected, 0 is returned.
.HP
\fB\-g\fR   \fB\-\-GraphicBox\fR: Displays a window with a 300x300 graphic.
.IP
Returns: Nothing
.HP
\fB\-p\fR   \fB\-\-ProgressBar\fR: Displays the progress of an action in 10% increments.
.IP
Returns: "cancel" if cancelled by user, otherwise nothing
.HP
\fB\-x\fR   \fB\-\-CopyToClipboard\fR: copy supplied text to system clipboard.
.IP
Built\-in alias: \fB\-\-Copy2Clipboard\fR
Returns: Nothing
.HP
\fB\-v\fR   \fB\-\-GetClipboard\fR: Retrieve text clipboard contents.
.IP
Returns: Clipboard content if that consists of text, otherwise
returns an empty string
.HP
\fB\-z\fR   \fB\-\-ViewClipboard\fR:Display current text clipboard contents in a
.IP
SimpleAlert window.
Returns: Nothing
.HP
\fB\-\-ColorControl\fR: Sets the color in which widgets will be displayed.
.IP
Returns: Nothing
.HP
\fB\-\-MakeContact\fR: Send me an email about yabdialog.
.HP
\fB\-h\fR   \fB\-\-help\fR: This HELP information.
.HP
\fB\-\-about\fR: Display an ABOUT dialog.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR > yabdialog.txt
save this help data to a text file.
.PP
COMMON OPTIONS
.PP
These options are compulsory and must precede specific options.
Options cannot be concatenated or omitted and must be entered in order.
.PP
\fB\-q[0\-9\fR|r|s]     Set the quadrant in which to display a widget.
.IP
\fB\-q0\fR \- centered
\fB\-q1\fR \- top left
\fB\-q2\fR \- top right
\fB\-q3\fR \- bottom right
\fB\-q4\fR \- bottom left
\fB\-q5\fR \- centered on all desktops
\fB\-q6\fR \- top left on all desktops
\fB\-q7\fR \- top right on all desktops
\fB\-q8\fR \- bottom right on all desktops
\fB\-q9\fR \- bottom left on all desktops
\fB\-qr\fR \- random position on current desktop
\fB\-qs\fR \- random position on all desktops
.PP
the r and s parameters are experimental and not recommended.
.HP
\fB\-b[0\fR|1|2]"|Message text"
.IP
\fB\-b0\fR Graphical button with checkmark
\fB\-b1Text\fR button with "OK"
\fB\-b2USERTEXT\fR Text button with user\-supplied text [1]
.PP
SPECIFIC OPTIONS
.PP
Specific options must be entered after the common options. Options
can not be concatenated or omitted and must be entered in order.
.PP
SIMPLEALERT
yabdialog \fB\-o\fR <common\-options> <text>
Example: yabdialog \fB\-s\fR \fB\-q1\fR \fB\-b1\fR "Click OK to make this message go away"
Example: yabdialog \fB\-s\fR \fB\-q1\fR \fB\-b2Ja\fR "Spreekt u Nederlands?"
Example: yabdialog \fB\-s\fR \fB\-q1\fR \fB\-b2\fRâ˜» "Smile! It's a beautiful day."
.PP
YESNOALERT
yabdialog \fB\-y\fR <common\-options> <text>
Example: yabdialog \fB\-y\fR \fB\-q1\fR \fB\-b0\fR "Will we watch football tonight?"
Example: yabdialog \fB\-y\fR \fB\-q1\fR \fB\-b1\fR "Will we watch football tonight?"
Example: yabdialog \fB\-y\fR \fB\-q1\fR \fB\-b2Ja\fR=\fI\,Nee\/\fR "Spreekt u Nederlands?"
Example: yabdialog \fB\-y\fR \fB\-q1\fR \fB\-b2Ja\fR=\fI\,Nein\/\fR "Sprechen Sie Deutsch?"
Example: yabdialog \fB\-y\fR \fB\-q1\fR \fB\-b2Oui\fR=\fI\,Non\/\fR "Parlez\-vous franÃ§ais?"
Example: yabdialog \fB\-y\fR \fB\-q1\fR \fB\-b2Si\fR=\fI\,No\/\fR "Â¿Habla usted espaÃ±ol?"[2]
.PP
OKCANCELALERT
yabdialog \fB\-o\fR <common\-options> <text> [3]
Example: yabdialog \fB\-o\fR \fB\-q1\fR \fB\-b0\fR "Delete the whole partition?"
Example: yabdialog \fB\-o\fR \fB\-q1\fR \fB\-b1\fR "Flash the BIOS?"
Example: yabdialog \fB\-o\fR \fB\-q1\fR \fB\-b2Sure\fR=\fI\,Never\/\fR! "Declare war on Linux?"
.PP
EDITOR
yabdialog \fB\-e\fR <common\-options> <content type> <content/file>
Common Options: only quadrants 0\-2 are available. Giving any
higher value will cause a default to 0
.TP
\fB\-t\fR <Initial Text>
OR
.HP
\fB\-f\fR <Initial Filename>
.PP
ONE of \fB\-t\fR or \fB\-f\fR MUST be supplied, but either the string or the file
may be empty.
Example: yabdialog \fB\-e\fR \fB\-q0\fR \fB\-b2Insert\fRÂ\ this \fB\-t\fR "This is some example text"
Example: yabdialog \fB\-e\fR \fB\-q1\fR \fB\-b0\fR \fB\-t\fR ""
Example: yabdialog \fB\-e\fR \fB\-q2\fR \fB\-b1\fR \fB\-f\fR "/boot/home/.bash_history"
This widget takes an OPTIONAL additional parameter, which becomes the
window title printed in the tab.
Example: yabdialog \fB\-e\fR \fB\-q1\fR \fB\-b1\fR \fB\-t\fR "example text" "The Editor"
.PP
TEXT INPUT
yabdialog \fB\-t\fR <common\-options> "Tab title"
Example: yabdialog \fB\-t\fR \fB\-q1\fR \fB\-b1\fR "What is your name?"
.PP
CALENDAR
yabdialog \fB\-c\fR <common\-options> <date\-format>
Date format consists of either MMDDYYY or DDMMYYY, with an optional
divider which can be one of ".", "/" or "\-". If no divider is supplied,
"." will be used. The return value will be supplied in the same format.
Example: yabdialog \fB\-c\fR \fB\-q6\fR \fB\-b3\fR DDMMYYYThis widget takes an OPTIONAL additional parameter, which becomes the
window title printed in the tab.
Example: yabdialog \fB\-c\fR \fB\-q0\fR \fB\-b0\fR MMDDYYY\- "Pick a date"
.PP
RADIOBOX
yabdialog \fB\-r\fR <common\-options> <number> <Radiobuttontext1> ...
Number is the number of radiobuttons (1\-5) you wish to create.
Radiobuttontext1 to Radiobuttontext5 contains the text to go next to
the radiobuttons.
Example:  yabdialog \fB\-r\fR \fB\-q6\fR \fB\-b1\fR 5 Haiku GNU/Linux "Windows 8" FreeBSD "I don't
.IP
like operating systems" "What is your favourite Operating System?"
.PP
GRAPHICBOX
yabdialog \fB\-g\fR <common\-options> <filename>
<filename> refers to a 300x300 .PNG file. If no filename is supplied,
yabdialog will look for the file \fI\,~/config/settings/yabdialog.png\/\fP.
This is meant for splash screens. Clicking either the graphic or the
button will dismiss the window.[5]
Example: yabdialog \fB\-g\fR \fB\-q3\fR \fB\-b0\fR "/boot/home/Desktop/clip.png"
.PP
PROGRESSBAR
yabdialog \fB\-p\fR <common\-options>  <windowtab text> <filename>
<windowtab text> is the text in the window's tab.
<filename> is a file containing a number between 0 and 9, and
nothing else, not even a newline. The program will exit when the
value in <filename> exceeds 9
Example: Run the following bash script
.IP
#!/bin/bash
echo 0 > \fI\,~/Desktop/temp.txt\/\fP
yabdialog \fB\-p\fR \fB\-q1\fR \fB\-b1\fR "Counting to 10 ..." \fI\,~/Desktop/temp.txt\/\fP &
for f in `seq 1 10`;
do
.IP
echo $f > \fI\,~/Desktop/temp.txt\/\fP
sleep 2
.IP
done
.PP
COPYTOCLIPBOARD
yabdialog \fB\-x\fR <text to copy to clipboard>
Example: yabdialog \fB\-x\fR "put this text on the clipboard, please."
.PP
GETCLIPBOARD
No additional parameters required.
Example: yabdialog \fB\-v\fR
.PP
VIEWCLIPBOARD
yabdialog \fB\-z\fR <common\-options>
Example: yabdialog \fB\-z\fR \fB\-q2\fR \fB\-b0\fR
.PP
COLORCONTROL
yabdialog \fB\-\-ColorControl\fR <color>
where <color> is one of white, yellow, blue, red, green or boring[6]
.IP
OR
.PP
yabdialog \fB\-\-ColorControl\fR custom <red> <green> <blue>
Example: yabdialog \fB\-\-ColorControl\fR white
Example: yabdialog \fB\-\-ColorControl\fR custom 240 150 200
All NEW widgets will be created in the new color.[7]
.PP
MAKECONTACT
No additional parameters required.
Example: yabdialog \fB\-\-MakeContact\fR
.PP
NOTES
1. The \fB\-b2\fR parameter is not available in the following widgets:
.IP
Calendar, Radiobox.
.PP
2. yabdialog \fB\-y\fR will return "yes" or "no" regardless of the button label!
3. The following two commands:
.TP
yabdialog \fB\-y\fR \fB\-q1\fR \fB\-b2Ja\fR=\fI\,Nein\/\fR "Sprechen Sie Deutsch?"
and
.IP
yabdialog \fB\-o\fR \fB\-q1\fR \fB\-b2Ja\fR=\fI\,Nein\/\fR "Sprechen Sie Deutsch?"
.IP
will produce identical dialogs, but present different values back
to the operating system or calling routine in your script language.
.PP
4. You can put labels of more than one word on widgets. The trick
.IP
is to use CHR 160 rather than the normal <space> which is CHR 32.
.PP
5. Alt\-Q will exit any yabdialog window and the program as a whole,
.IP
even in tabless windows. Dealing with the lack of a return value
will be your problem.
.PP
6. The color "boring" is the standard medium grey Haiku dialog tint,
.IP
i.e. r=216 g=216 b=216. It is also the starting default.
.PP
7. Color changes will persist across reboots! Remember to switch the
.IP
yabdialog color back to "boring" (see above) or to delete the file
\fI\,/boot/home/config/settings/yabdialog.cfg\/\fP when you are done.
